The paper deals with the issue of accurately tracking the location of moving objects in sensor networks with energy constraints. This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR) as the paper discusses the need for controlling and maintaining data and the limited wireless communication bandwidth. The use of prediction and adaptive algorithms also suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the extension of network lifetime, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
